description: This is a beautiful and tough trek, you will be rewarded with great scenery everyday such as majestic peaks like Ama Dablam and Pumori, valleys, suspension bridges, and much more. One of the world’s greatest treks. An easy tea house trail to follow, over and down and along Himalayan valleys, finally walking to over 4100M. Views are spectacular weather permitting. Here you will be able to see Nayapul, Ghorepani, Poon Hill, Ghandruk, and Chomrong.This path will additionally lead you via the Annapurna Conservation Area, the place where you will be able to spot uncommon animals like the crimson panda and Himalayan monal with a backdrop of lush greenery and shaded forest. The mighty Annapurna is known to be the best possible mountain in the world.  The charming Annapurna massif consists of the world’s tenth absolute best peak.
